WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:00.920
A

00:30.000 --> 00:35.000
Excuse me.

00:35.000 --> 00:37.000
My name is Richard Stewart.

00:37.000 --> 00:38.000
I'm a photographer.

00:38.000 --> 00:40.000
May I take a picture of you and your little boy?

00:40.000 --> 00:41.000
What's it for?

00:41.000 --> 00:42.000
That's for a book.

00:42.000 --> 00:43.000
You're writing a book?

00:43.000 --> 00:44.000
Oh, head.

00:44.000 --> 00:45.000
It's a book of pictures.

00:45.000 --> 00:47.000
I call it family album USA.

00:47.000 --> 00:49.000
Oh, that's a nice idea.

00:49.000 --> 00:51.000
Well, it's fun if you take our picture.

00:51.000 --> 00:52.000
I'm Martha Van.

00:52.000 --> 00:53.000
Thank you.

00:53.000 --> 00:55.000
I appreciate your help.

00:55.000 --> 00:56.000
I'm Richard.

00:56.000 --> 00:57.000
What's your name?

00:57.000 --> 00:58.000
Daryl.

00:58.000 --> 00:59.000
How old are you, Gerald?

00:59.000 --> 01:00.000
Bye.

01:00.000 --> 01:01.000
And where do you live?

01:01.000 --> 01:03.000
We live in California.

01:03.000 --> 01:05.000
Well, welcome to New York.

01:05.000 --> 01:08.000
Okay, just a second.

01:08.000 --> 01:11.000
I'm almost ready here.

01:11.000 --> 01:12.000
I'm almost ready.

01:12.000 --> 01:13.000
Oh, please.

01:13.000 --> 01:16.000
Hey, hold Gerald's hand, please.

01:16.000 --> 01:18.000
Great.

01:18.000 --> 01:21.000
Now, point to the building.

01:21.000 --> 01:23.000
I'm going to go to the building.

01:23.000 --> 01:25.000
I'm going to go to the building.

01:26.000 --> 01:28.000
Great.

01:28.000 --> 01:32.000
Now, point to the buildings.

01:32.000 --> 01:36.000
Terrific.

01:36.000 --> 01:40.000
And give Mommy a kiss, Gerald.

01:40.000 --> 01:43.000
Nice.

01:43.000 --> 01:45.000
Thank you, Gerald.

01:45.000 --> 01:47.000
And thank you, Mrs. Van.

01:47.000 --> 01:48.000
Oh, my pleasure.

01:48.000 --> 01:50.000
We'll be looking for your book.

01:50.000 --> 01:51.000
Thank you.

01:51.000 --> 01:52.000
Goodbye.

01:52.000 --> 01:54.000
Bye, Gerald.

01:55.000 --> 01:57.000
Thanks again.

01:57.000 --> 01:59.000
Oh, you're welcome.

01:59.000 --> 02:01.000
Hey, let me take your picture.

02:01.000 --> 02:03.000
Wonderful, please.

02:03.000 --> 02:11.000
Are you from New York?

02:11.000 --> 02:12.000
No, I'm from Greece.

02:12.000 --> 02:14.000
I'm an exchange student.

02:14.000 --> 02:16.000
What did you come here?

02:16.000 --> 02:18.000
Three months ago.

02:18.000 --> 02:20.000
Your English is very good.

02:20.000 --> 02:21.000
Thanks.

02:21.000 --> 02:23.000
I studied English in school.

02:23.000 --> 02:28.000
When you like some coffee?

02:28.000 --> 02:30.000
No, thank you.

02:30.000 --> 02:32.000
Tell me about your book.

02:32.000 --> 02:34.000
Oh, it's not finished yet.

02:34.000 --> 02:36.000
But I have some of the pictures.

02:36.000 --> 02:37.000
Would you like to see them?

02:37.000 --> 02:38.000
Yes, I'd like that.

02:38.000 --> 02:41.000
Oh, there they are.

02:41.000 --> 02:46.000
Family album USA.

02:46.000 --> 02:48.000
It's an album of pictures of the United States,

02:48.000 --> 02:51.000
the cities, the special places, and the people.

02:51.000 --> 02:54.000
And these are pictures of people working.

02:54.000 --> 03:03.000
Steel workers, bankers, police, street vendors,

03:03.000 --> 03:08.000
ambulance truck, doctors.

03:08.000 --> 03:10.000
Oh, this is my father.

03:10.000 --> 03:13.000
He's a doctor.

03:13.000 --> 03:15.000
This is my mother.

03:15.000 --> 03:16.000
What's her name?

03:16.000 --> 03:17.000
Allen.

03:17.000 --> 03:22.000
My younger brother, Robbie, he goes to high school.

03:22.000 --> 03:24.000
This is my sister, Susan.

03:24.000 --> 03:28.000
She works for a toy company.

03:28.000 --> 03:30.000
Here's my grandfather.

03:30.000 --> 03:32.000
He lives in Florida.

03:32.000 --> 03:34.000
And this is my wife, Marilyn.

03:34.000 --> 03:36.000
Oh, she's very pretty.

03:36.000 --> 03:37.000
Thanks.

03:37.000 --> 03:39.000
And what about your family?

03:39.000 --> 03:42.000
They are in the Thessaloniki.

03:42.000 --> 03:45.000
That's a large city in northern Greece.

03:45.000 --> 03:48.000
But now I'm living in the Bronx.

03:48.000 --> 03:50.000
With a Greek-American family?

03:50.000 --> 03:52.000
No, Hispanic.

03:52.000 --> 03:57.000
Oh, no.

03:57.000 --> 03:59.000
It's 5.30.

03:59.000 --> 04:01.000
Um, will you excuse me?

04:01.000 --> 04:02.000
I have to meet my wife.

04:02.000 --> 04:03.000
It's nice meeting you.

04:03.000 --> 04:05.000
Oh, it's a pleasure meeting you, too.

04:05.000 --> 04:06.000
Thanks for your help.

04:06.000 --> 04:08.000
And good luck.

04:08.000 --> 04:09.000
I've got to go.

04:09.000 --> 04:10.000
By the way, I'm Richard.

04:10.000 --> 04:11.000
What's your name?

04:11.000 --> 04:12.000
Alexandra.

04:12.000 --> 04:14.000
Bye-bye, Alexandra.

04:14.000 --> 04:16.000
Bye-bye, Alexandra.

04:16.000 --> 04:17.000
Bye-bye.

04:17.000 --> 04:18.000
Bye-bye.

04:18.000 --> 04:19.000
Richard.

04:19.000 --> 04:21.000
Richard, you left your bag.

04:21.000 --> 04:23.000
Richard, you left your bag.

04:23.000 --> 04:24.000
Oh, my God.

